## Global system of connected computer networks

This article, mind you, is about the *worldwide computer network*. If you’re looking for that global system of pages accessed through URLs via the Internet, that’s the [World Wide Web](/World_Wide_Web). And no, don’t even think about calling it the "Interweb" unless you want to be corrected with extreme prejudice. That term redirects here, so at least the system has a semblance of order.

There are… *issues* with this article. Apparently, it needs more *verification*. As if the sheer existence of this sprawling mess of interconnectedness isn't proof enough. And it needs to be *updated*. Because, naturally, something this fluid and chaotic is impossible to pin down permanently.

